An {\textbf{{ambient isotopy}}} $H$ is of a PL-manifold $X$ is a collection of homeomorphisms $H_t:  X \rightarrow X$  for $t \in [0,1]$, which vary continuously with $t$, and with $H_0 = {\ensuremath{\text{id}}}$. We say that an ambient isotopy $H$ {\textbf{{throws}}} a subspace $Y \subseteq X$ onto $Z$ if $H_1(Y)=Z$, see \cite[Ch.~V]{Zeeman:Seminar-on-combinatorial-topology-1966}. 

We say that an ambient isotopy $H$ of $X$ is {\textbf{{proper}}} if  $H_t |_{{\ensuremath{\partial}} X} = {\ensuremath{\text{id}}}_{{\ensuremath{\partial}} X}$  for all~$t$.

